goals.question: What is the correlation between fertility and life expectancy?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of fertility vs life_expect
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to understand if there is any relationship between fertility and life expectancy. A positive correlation would indicate that countries with higher fertility rates tend to have lower life expectancies and vice versa.

goals.question: What is the distribution of fertility across different countries?
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to understand the spread of fertility rates across different countries. It can help identify countries with high or low fertility rates and understand the overall distribution.

goals.question: What is the trend of life expectancy over the years?
goals.visualization: Line chart of life_expect over year
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to understand the trend of life expectancy over the years. It can help identify if there has been any improvement or decline in life expectancy over time.

goals.question: What is the relationship between fertility and country development?
goals.visualization: Box plot of fertility by country
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to understand if there is any relationship between fertility rates and country development. It can help identify if developed countries tend to have lower fertility rates compared to developing countries.

goals.question: What is the distribution of life expectancy across different countries?

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.scatter(data['fertility'], data['life_expect'], alpha=0.5, color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Fertility')
    ax.set_ylabel('Life Expectancy')
    ax.set_title('What is the correlation between fertility and life expectancy?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data) # data already contains the data to be plotted. Always include this line. DO NOT modify the rest of the code template.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 8))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='fertility', hue='country', ax=ax, kde=True, multiple='stack', palette='bright')
    ax.set_xlabel('Fertility')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of fertility across different countries?', wrap=True)
    ax.legend(title='Country', loc='upper right', bbox_to_anchor=(1.25, 1))
    ax.axvline(data['fertility'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {data["fertility"].median():.2f}')
    return plt

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y')
    data = data.sort_values(by='year')
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['life_expect'], color='blue')
    plt.axhline(y=data['life_expect'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Median Life Expectancy')
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Life Expectancy')
    plt.title('What is the trend of life expectancy over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 8))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='life_expect', hue='country', kde=True, ax=ax)
    ax.axvline(data['life_expect'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Mean Life Expectancy: {:.2f}'.format(data['life_expect'].mean()))
    ax.set_xlabel('Life Expectancy')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of life expectancy across different countries?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
